<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
  <title>{{ product_name }} - White-label weekly website reports</title>
  <style>
    :root {
      --ink: #172033;
      --muted: #5f6b7a;
      --line: #d9e0ea;
      --paper: #ffffff;
      --wash: #f6f8fb;
      --accent: #147a68;
      --accent-dark: #0e574c;
      --warn: #a45b13;
    }
    * { box-sizing: border-box; }
    body {
      margin: 0;
      font-family: Inter, ui-sans-serif, system-ui, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "Segoe UI", sans-serif;
      color: var(--ink);
      background: var(--paper);
      line-height: 1.5;
    }
    a { color: inherit; }
    .shell { max-width: 1120px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 0 24px; }
    header {
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line);
      background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.95);
      position: sticky;
      top: 0;
      z-index: 2;
    }
    .nav {
      height: 64px;
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      justify-content: space-between;
      gap: 16px;
    }
    .brand { font-weight: 760; letter-spacing: 0; }
    .nav-links { display: flex; gap: 18px; color: var(--muted); font-size: 14px; }
    .hero {
      padding: 72px 0 52px;
      background: linear-gradient(180deg, #eef7f4 0%, #ffffff 78%);
    }
    .hero-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1.08fr) minmax(320px, 0.92fr);
      gap: 44px;
      align-items: center;
    }
    .eyebrow {
      margin: 0 0 12px;
      color: var(--accent-dark);
      font-size: 14px;
      font-weight: 700;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      letter-spacing: 0;
    }
    h1 {
      margin: 0;
      font-size: clamp(36px, 6vw, 62px);
      line-height: 1.02;
      letter-spacing: 0;
      max-width: 820px;
    }
    .lead {
      max-width: 700px;
      margin: 22px 0 0;
      color: var(--muted);
      font-size: 20px;
    }
    .actions { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 12px; margin-top: 30px; }
    .button {
      display: inline-flex;
      min-height: 44px;
      align-items: center;
      justify-content: center;
      border-radius: 8px;
      border: 1px solid var(--accent);
      padding: 10px 16px;
      text-decoration: none;
      font-weight: 700;
      font-size: 15px;
    }
    .button.primary { background: var(--accent); color: #fff; }
    .button.primary:hover { background: var(--accent-dark); }
    .button.secondary { background: #fff; color: var(--accent-dark); }
    .proof {
      margin-top: 24px;
      color: var(--muted);
      font-size: 14px;
    }
    .report-preview {
      background: var(--paper);
      border: 1px solid var(--line);
      border-radius: 8px;
      box-shadow: 0 20px 70px rgba(23, 32, 51, 0.12);
      overflow: hidden;
    }
    .preview-top {
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 8px;
      height: 40px;
      padding: 0 14px;
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line);
      background: #f9fbfd;
    }
    .dot { width: 8px; height: 8px; border-radius: 50%; background: #9aa6b2; }
    .preview-body { padding: 22px; }
    .score-row {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 120px 1fr;
      gap: 18px;
      align-items: center;
      margin-bottom: 18px;
    }
    .score {
      display: grid;
      place-items: center;
      aspect-ratio: 1;
      border-radius: 8px;
      background: #eaf6f1;
      color: var(--accent-dark);
      font-size: 34px;
      font-weight: 800;
    }
    .mini-title { margin: 0 0 4px; font-weight: 760; }
    .mini-copy { margin: 0; color: var(--muted); font-size: 14px; }
    .check-list { display: grid; gap: 10px; margin: 18px 0 0; padding: 0; list-style: none; }
    .check-list li {
      border: 1px solid var(--line);
      border-radius: 8px;
      padding: 10px 12px;
      font-size: 14px;
      background: #fff;
    }
    section { padding: 64px 0; }
    section.alt { background: var(--wash); border-top: 1px solid var(--line); border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line); }
    h2 { margin: 0 0 18px; font-size: 32px; letter-spacing: 0; }
    .section-copy { max-width: 760px; margin: 0 0 28px; color: var(--muted); font-size: 17px; }
    .benefits {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(3, minmax(0, 1fr));
      gap: 14px;
    }
    .benefit, .plan {
      background: var(--paper);
      border: 1px solid var(--line);
      border-radius: 8px;
      padding: 20px;
    }
    .benefit strong { display: block; margin-bottom: 6px; }
    .benefit p, .plan p { margin: 0; color: var(--muted); }
    .plans {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(3, minmax(0, 1fr));
      gap: 16px;
    }
    .plan.featured { border-color: var(--accent); box-shadow: inset 0 4px 0 var(--accent); }
    .plan h3 { margin: 0 0 8px; font-size: 22px; }
    .price { margin: 12px 0 16px; font-size: 34px; font-weight: 800; }
    .price span { color: var(--muted); font-size: 15px; font-weight: 600; }
    .plan .button { width: 100%; margin-top: 18px; }
    .note {
      margin-top: 18px;
      color: var(--warn);
      font-size: 14px;
    }
    .steps {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(3, minmax(0, 1fr));
      gap: 20px;
      counter-reset: steps;
    }
    .step {
      border-top: 3px solid var(--accent);
      padding-top: 14px;
    }
    .step::before {
      counter-increment: steps;
      content: counter(steps);
      display: inline-grid;
      place-items: center;
      width: 28px;
      height: 28px;
      border-radius: 50%;
      background: var(--accent);
      color: #fff;
      font-weight: 800;
      margin-bottom: 10px;
    }
    footer { padding: 34px 0; color: var(--muted); border-top: 1px solid var(--line); }
    @media (max-width: 860px) {
      .hero-grid, .benefits, .plans, .steps { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
      .hero { padding-top: 44px; }
      .nav-links { display: none; }
      .score-row { grid-template-columns: 92px 1fr; }
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <header>
    <div class="shell nav">
      <div class="brand">{{ product_name }}</div>
      <nav class="nav-links" aria-label="Main navigation">
        <a href="#report">Report</a>
        <a href="#pricing">Pricing</a>
        <a href="#faq">FAQ</a>
        <a href="#start">Start</a>
        <a href="/client/login">Client login</a>
      </nav>
    </div>
  </header>

  <main>
    <section class="hero">
      <div class="shell hero-grid">
        <div>
          <p class="eyebrow">{{ positioning }}</p>
          <h1>Weekly website reports your clients can actually read.</h1>
          <p class="lead">
            {{ primary_offer }} for {{ target_audience }}. This is a reporting service, not another dashboard:
            every week you receive a client-ready report with site status, basic SEO, broken links,
            form checks, weekly changes, a health score, and the next 3 actions.
          </p>
          <div class="actions">
            <a class="button primary" href="#pricing">Choose a plan</a>
            {% if demo_report_path %}
            <a class="button secondary" href="{{ demo_report_path }}">View sample report</a>
            {% endif %}
            <a class="button secondary" href="/client/login">Client login</a>
          </div>
          <p class="proof">Built for service businesses that need client-ready proof of work every week without preparing reports from scratch.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="report-preview" id="report" aria-label="Sample report preview">
          <div class="preview-top"><span class="dot"></span><span class="dot"></span><span class="dot"></span></div>
          <div class="preview-body">
            <div class="score-row">
              <div class="score">82</div>
              <div>
                <p class="mini-title">Site Health Score</p>
                <p class="mini-copy">A simple client-facing summary backed by deterministic checks.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <ul class="check-list">
              <li><strong>Action 1:</strong> Fix newly broken internal links.</li>
              <li><strong>Action 2:</strong> Update missing meta descriptions.</li>
              <li><strong>Action 3:</strong> Review slow pages before the next campaign.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section>
      <div class="shell">
        <h2>What you get every week</h2>
        <p class="section-copy">A client-ready report under your brand, generated from repeatable checks and designed to be sent as-is or lightly reviewed before delivery.</p>
        <div class="benefits">
          {% for benefit in main_benefits %}
          <div class="benefit">
            <strong>{{ benefit }}</strong>
            <p>Included in the weekly reporting workflow.</p>
          </div>
          {% endfor %}
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="alt" id="pricing">
      <div class="shell">
        <h2>Pricing</h2>
        <p class="section-copy">Start with a sample report, then subscribe when you want reports prepared every week for your client sites.</p>
        <div class="plans">
          {% for plan in plans %}
          <article class="plan{% if plan.id == 'agency-lite' %} featured{% endif %}">
            <h3>{{ plan.name }}</h3>
            <p>{{ plan.description }}</p>
            <div class="price">{{ currency }} {{ plan.price }}<span>/mo</span></div>
            {% if plan.checkout_url %}
            <a class="button primary" href="{{ plan.checkout_url }}">Subscribe</a>
            {% else %}
            <a class="button secondary" href="{{ signup_url }}?plan={{ plan.id | urlencode }}">Start setup</a>
            {% endif %}
          </article>
          {% endfor %}
        </div>
        <p class="note">Setup fee can be added manually for onboarding, branding, and the first reviewed report. Without checkout URLs, plan buttons open the setup form.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    {% if demo_reports %}
    <section>
      <div class="shell">
        <h2>Demo reports</h2>
        <p class="section-copy">Use these examples to see how the report reads for a healthy site, a site that needs attention, and a problematic site.</p>
        <div class="benefits">
          {% for demo in demo_reports %}
          <div class="benefit">
            <strong>{{ demo.split('/')[-1].replace('_', ' ').replace('.html', '').title() }}</strong>
            <p><a href="{{ demo }}">Open demo report</a></p>
          </div>
          {% endfor %}
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
    {% endif %}

    <section id="start">
      <div class="shell">
        <h2>How onboarding works</h2>
        <div class="steps">
          <div class="step">
            <h3>Sample report</h3>
            <p>Run a one-off report for the prospect site and send the result manually.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="step">
            <h3>Checkout and setup</h3>
            <p>The client chooses a website count, pays through checkout, and submits site and branding details.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="step">
            <h3>Portal and delivery</h3>
            <p>The client can log in to view sites, reports, billing status, and request setting changes while reports are prepared weekly.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="alt" id="faq">
      <div class="shell">
        <h2>FAQ</h2>
        <div class="benefits">
          <div class="benefit">
            <strong>Is this a full SEO audit?</strong>
            <p>No. It is a weekly monitoring and reporting service for availability, SEO basics, links, forms, changes, and prioritized actions.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="benefit">
            <strong>Do clients need another dashboard?</strong>
            <p>No. Reports are ready to send. The client portal is for viewing reports, sites, billing status, and requesting small setting changes.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="benefit">
            <strong>Can this run under my brand?</strong>
            <p>Yes. Reports support brand name, color, logo, footer text, and client-specific delivery settings.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="benefit">
            <strong>Does it replace Ahrefs or Search Console?</strong>
            <p>No. It complements those tools with a client-readable weekly operational report.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="benefit">
            <strong>Can I review before sending?</strong>
            <p>Yes. The operator workflow prepares reports and outbox drafts first; sending can remain manual.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="benefit">
            <strong>What happens if payment fails?</strong>
            <p>Payment status is tracked and inactive clients can be skipped from weekly delivery.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  <footer>
    <div class="shell">
      {{ product_name }} - generated {{ generated_at }}. Contact: <a href="mailto:{{ contact_email }}">{{ contact_email }}</a>.
    </div>
  </footer>
</body>
</html>
